"Do not trade in your phone or be convinced to wipe data if you do buy an iPhone. Rely on your yourself and not AppleHere is my detailed experience with Apple recently. Please do not trade in or wipe your phone even if you are being advised to do so. Apple Sales/Customer Service has lost it:I have been a long time Apple customer (iphone, iPad, MacBook Pro). Just bought a new iPhone 15 Pro yesterday (6th April) and here is my frustrating experience with the sales and customer service team at Regent Street store. Firstly, be aware that the new iPhone only comes with a cable - USB-C connector which requires you to buy a separate socket to use in the UK and cannot be used on its own while travelling (on flights, trains, buses etc). This was explained to me by one guy (who apologetically said he is not responsible for making decisions) that Apple was trying to reduce carbon footprint by not wanting to manufacture a bigger box to include the socket. Makes no sense since they are manufacturing a whole new box and charging customers for it. I get it that this is a sales tactic and Apple has made more money and saved with this strategy. Just think that if you are paying an exorbitant price for an iPhone - it would seem fair to have the necessary cables and sockets to easily charge at home without dishing out more.                                                                                 My first question to the sales associate was if my data will get transferred to the new iPhone and this guy kept assuring me it will. He also tells me that I will get £30 for my old phone after checking it and says I can trade in. I was wary of this as I wanted to make sure my data got transferred. I checked to see if any other corporate or company discount applied. And in the new iPhone series it doesn’t.                                        I was guided to the ‘genius bar’ area where data transfer was taking place for a number of people with new devices. And the most common phrase I heard used was that the set-up is complete and the data will continue getting transferred as long as you are on wifi. I stayed for roughly about an hour and half trying to get this sorted and the guy who was coordinating this tells me that the phone is set up and all the data is getting transferred. I asked me over and over again if he is sure that the data will get transferred including mentioning my profession and how important this is. His response – “I have been doing this every day and this is how its done. All your data has been transferred” Note that this is a phone to phone transfer. I felt like they were trying to rush everyone out. I ask him if my phone can be traded in now and he says yes (and I ask again about my data transfer and he is annoyed with me and says that all the data has been transferred), let’s wipe the phone which he then proceeds to do and tells me his colleagues on the floor below will help with the trade in.                                                                                          When I go downstairs – I’m assigned another person who says he will trade it in and runs through a series of checks. After about 10-15 minutes he tells me I can’t trade it in because the touch button doesn’t work so I ask him why didn’t they let me know this before and why did they wipe my phone if that was the case. He tells me they shouldn’t have done that and I can restore it from my new phone if I like. Its almost closing time and I was quite annoyed so I buy one of the £19 socket and leave. This guy selling me the socket tells me that it’s the EU which has made them change to new cable (charging) and that they have reduced the price of iphone because the socket is not included!                                                                        When I go home, after a couple of hours I realise that no data from my ‘Signal’ app is downloaded and because it is an encrypted app – the message I’m getting is to scan from my old iphone to download previous history and numbers.                                              To read what happened next, please go to Reddit under the headline (APPLE CUSTOMER SERVICE / iPhone 15 - REGENT STREET LONDON) - I can't post  more here due to word limit.Date of experience:April 06, 2024",3,Bharati,1,United Kingdom,2024-04-09 00:00:00.000000,detailed long new pro regent aware new separate responsible whole new tactic exorbitant fair necessary first new old wary sure transferred see corporate new new common complete stayed transferred sure important wipe touch ask new quite new signal scan old previous next due,Positive
