d, I just don’t want the product anymore. Without a laptop I have been totally incapable of completing assignments and revising for exams, this is a significant inconvenience. Alongside this, I have had to drive to and from an apple store twice, of which take one hour each way to commute to, I have had no expenses refunded to me despite this being a fault with the product from their end, paying for parking every time I visit the store (4 times now). I have spent over 20 hours on the phone to different apple support advisors, none of which have ever met me with a mutually amicable agreement. I have been told to await a call back from an advisor, only to never receive one. I have expressed my frustration, anxiety and stress over this faulty product and the detrimental impact it has had on my studies, which has been completely ignored by the apple team.I have explained that I no longer want this Apple Mac product, I quoted the consumer rights act 2015 and the final right to reject, all of which were ignored by the apple team as they refused to refund/replace. I have undergone one replacement which was unsuccessful and lengthy, therefore my claim falls under the final right to reject. Apple have stated the repair was done under the warranty, however I did not consent to this. I wanted the repair and the following case to be dealt with under the consumer rights act 2015, which would therefore give me the right to a refund/replacement. The reason apple have used the warranty instead is to void my right to a replacement or refund. Apple have told me that my only option now is to wait another week, drive another 2 hours, drop the MacBook off at the same service provider that didn’t initially fix it, be without a MacBook (or any laptop) for another week (despite having exams next week and moving location every 3 weeks because I am on my final year rotations), only to commute again, pay for parking again, to retrieve a product I no longer want and be a significant loss (time,